cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new automatic evaluation metric for text generation, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The use of contextual embeddings and machine learning models suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The evaluation of machine translation and image captioning systems suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of an adversarial paraphrase detection task suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
